[style name="res://Dialogue/Styles/CozyPersonaVN.tres"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The morning sun shines over the quiet neighborhood.
A sedan is parked neatly outside the Ilagan house.
The street is calm. A few neighbors sweep their front yards while children walk toward school.
The front gate slowly opens.
Ethan walks toward the house carrying a small paper bag from a local bakery.
He pauses for a moment before ringing the doorbell.
DING DONG.
[signal arg="sfx:doorbell"]
A few seconds pass.
The door opens.
Ricardo stands at the doorway.
His expression immediately softens.
Ethan. Maaga ka ah.
Chuckling.
May dala po akong pandesal.
Fresh pa.
Ricardo smiles.
Aba... Sakto.
Kape na lang kulang.
Pasok ka na, hijo.
Ethan steps inside.
The house feels unusually quiet.
The television is off.
No music plays.
The silence feels heavier than usual.
Ethan notices Jennifer arranging a few things on a nearby shelf.
Ethan notices Jennifer standing near the living room.
She's looking down at her phone.
Her thumb scrolls absentmindedly through social media.
Good morning po, Tita.
Jennifer doesn't respond immediately.
Still focused on her screen.
A beat passes.
She suddenly looks up.
Ay...
Good morning, Ethan.
Pasensya na.
Ethan smiles politely.
Okay lang po.
He hands her the paper bag.
May pandesal po.
Naku.
Hindi na sana nag-abala.
Okay lang po.
Napadaan lang.
Jennifer smiles politely.
But her eyes betray her exhaustion.
She hasn't been sleeping well.
Ethan notices.
He doesn't mention it.
Instead...
Nasaan po si Maya?
Jennifer pauses.
She glances toward the hallway.
Nasa kwarto pa nya..
Ethan nods.
The answer is enough.
Ricardo walks toward the kitchen.
Kape muna tayo.
Baka magising din 'yon si Maya.
The aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the room.
The paper bag of pandesal sits in the middle of the table.
Jennifer begins serving everyone.
The atmosphere is noticeably lighter than it has been in days.
Buti napadaan ka, Ethan.
Hindi ka na masyadong nakakabisita rito.
Medyo naging busy lang po.
Thesis.
Requirements.
Alam n'yo naman.
Ricardo nods absentmindedly.
His phone vibrates beside his coffee.
[signal arg="sfx:phone_notif"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
He glances at the screen.
A customer asking for an update on a repair.
Without thinking...
He begins typing a reply.
Raising an eyebrow.
Hon...
Mamaya na 'yan.
Kumakain tayo.
Ricardo looks up.
As if only now realizing what he was doing.
Ah. Sorry.
He locks his phone and sets it beside his plate.
Smiles.
Okay lang po, Tito.
Work is work.
Chuckles sheepishly.
Sensya na, minsan...nadadala lang talaga.
Normal lang 'yan.
Last stretch na.
Konting tiis na lang.
Ethan nods.
Jennifer smiles proudly.
She glances toward Maya's empty seat.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
Gano'n din si Maya.
Halos hindi na nga lumalabas ng kwarto kakaaral.
Kung minsan kailangan ko pang pilitin magpahinga.
Ricardo smiles.
Mana sa sipag.
Jennifer chuckles.
Kaya nga kahit nahihirapan...
Alam kong kakayanin niya.
Hindi naman basta sumusuko ang anak namin.
Ethan smiles politely.
He hesitates.
Unsure whether to say anything.
Then...
Actually po... Okay na ba siya?
The room grows quieter.
Jennifer looks at him. Confused.
Anong ibig mong sabihin?
Ethan blinks.
He immediately realizes something is off.
Ah...
Akala ko po... Nasabi na niya.
Jennifer slowly lowers her spoon.
Nasabi ang alin?
Ethan looks between Jennifer and Ricardo.
Then toward the hallway.
His expression changes.
He wasn't supposed to be the one saying it.
He remembers the message Maya sent him weeks ago, venting about the failed requirement.
He assumed that if she told him, she'd told them too.
He never considered that texting him had been the safer version of the truth.
...
About po doon sa...major requirement niya.
Silence.
Ricardo frowns.
Anong requirement?
Ethan swallows.
His voice becomes quieter.
Yung... Hindi niya po naipasa.
The room falls completely silent.
Jennifer stares at him.
As if she misheard.
...
Ano?
Ethan quickly shakes his head.
Tita... Akala ko talaga alam n'yo na.
I'm sorry.
Jennifer slowly stands.
Her eyes remain fixed on Ethan.
Hindi niya sinabi sa'min.
Ricardo's expression hardens.
He looks toward the hallway leading to Maya's room.
A mixture of confusion...
And disappointment.
Kailan pa nangyari 'to?
Ethan rubs the back of his neck.
Clearly uncomfortable.
Matagal na po.
I... I thought napag-usapan niyo na.
Nobody responds.
The silence becomes unbearable.
Jennifer slowly exhales.
Trying to process everything.
So...
Habang sinasabi niyang okay lang siya... Habang sinasabi niyang kaya niya...
Hindi pala totoo.
Ricardo doesn't answer.
His jaw tightens.
For the first time...
Neither parent knows what to believe anymore.
Ethan looks toward Maya's closed bedroom door.
Guilt washes over him.
He never intended to expose her.
He simply assumed...
Her parents already knew.
Instead...
He had revealed the truth himself.
And in doing so...
The trust inside the Ilagan household quietly began to crumble.
The dining table remains untouched.
The cups of coffee have gone cold.
Ricardo sits at the head of the table.
Jennifer quietly folds a dish towel in her hands, more out of nervousness than necessity.
Ethan sits across from them.
No one says a word.
Ricardo breaks the silence.
Hindi puwedeng ganito na lang, Jen.
Jennifer looks up and sighs.
Alam ko pero-.
Pause.
-pero hindi ko alam kung paano magsisimula.
Ricardo nods in agreement.
Ethan looks toward the hallway.
Maybe...
Hindi niyo kailangang alam agad ang tamang sasabihin.
Baka...
kailangan lang muna niyang maramdaman na gusto niyo siyang pakinggan.
Jennifer slowly lowers her eyes.
She quietly nods.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
A soft knock is heard.
Anak...
Pwede ba tayong mag-usap?
Maya looks up from her phone and towards the door.
She takes a deep breath.
[signal arg="sfx:breath_shaky"]
... Sige po.
Ricardo opens the door slowly.
Jennifer stands beside him.
She looks hesitant.
Almost unsure if she's welcome.
Ethan quietly stays behind in the hallway.
Giving the family space.
Ricardo gestures toward the living room.
Labas muna tayo.
Usap lang.
Walang sigawan.
Walang sermon.
Maya studies her parents for a moment.
Then quietly nods.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The three sit facing each other.
Ricardo takes the single armchair.
Maya and Jennifer sit on opposite ends of the sofa.
The distance between them feels much farther than a few feet.
Nobody speaks.
Until...
Anak...
Hindi namin gustong matapos 'yung usapan natin kagabi nang gano'n.
Maya looks down.
Sorry po.
Hindi ka dapat unang humihingi ng sorry.
Maya looks up.
Ricardo gives her a gentle smile.
Gusto lang naming maintindihan.
Pause.
Simulan natin ulit.
Maya takes a deep breath.
[signal arg="sfx:breath_shaky"]
She grips the sleeve of her hoodie.
Trying to steady herself.
The grip on her phone tightens.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
Then, slowly, she sets it face down on the cushion beside her, choosing, for once, to sit with the feeling instead of escaping it.
I've been thinking about this...
for a long time.
Nung first year pa lang...
nahihirapan na talaga ako.
Pero sabi ko...
baka adjustment lang.
Pause.
Second year...
mas lalo akong nahirapan.
Tapos sabi ko ulit...
baka kaya ko pa.
Her voice begins to shake.
Hanggang sa...
dumating na lang sa point na...
gumigising na lang ako...
na parang ayoko nang pumasok.
Jennifer quietly listens.
She doesn't interrupt.
For the first time...
She lets Maya finish.
Hindi dahil tamad ako.
Hindi dahil ayoko mag-aral.
Pause.
Pagod na pagod na lang talaga ako.
Maya wipes away a tear.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Every exam...
pakiramdam ko...
kapag nagkamali ako...
madidisappoint ko kayo.
Every project...
pakiramdam ko...
hindi sapat.
Her breathing becomes uneven.
Tapos...
nakikita ko si Ethan.
Maya glances briefly toward the hallway.
Ang dali niyang kausap.
Magaling siya sa school.
Nagagawa niyang tumulong kay Dad sa shop.
Kahit may pinagdadaanan siya...
parang kaya pa rin niya.
Pause.
Napapaisip tuloy ako...
Bakit ako hindi?
The room falls silent.
join Jennifer (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Jennifer's expression softens.
She remembers the photos.
The repair shop.
Ricardo smiling beside Ethan.
She finally understands why those moments hurt Maya.
Hindi ko naman siya sinisisi.
Never.
He's my best friend.
Pero...
Hindi ko mapigilan ikumpara sarili ko.
Her voice becomes quieter.
Parang...
kahit anong gawin ko...
lagi akong kulang.
Long silence.
Jennifer slowly inhales.
She fights the urge to respond immediately.
Instead...
She lets Maya talk.
Maya's eyes fall toward her hands.
A faint smile appears.
The first genuine smile she's shown since the conversation began.
Kapag nagdo-drawing ako...
Tahimik.
Walang pressure.
Walang grades.
Walang expectations.
Ako lang.
Pause.
Hindi ko namamalayan 'yung oras.
Hindi ko iniisip kung sapat ba ako.
I just...
feel happy.
The words linger.
update Jennifer (worried)
Jennifer looks down.
Her eyes begin to glisten.
She remembers the little girl who proudly held up every drawing she made.
She remembers hanging them on the refrigerator.
She remembers...
What a creative soul she is deep down.
Hindi ko alam kung anong mangyayari.
Hindi ko rin alam kung kaya ko pa.
Pero...
Alam ko na...
na hindi ko kayang magsinungaling sa sarili ko habang buhay.
The room falls completely silent.
No one rushes to answer.
No one argues.
Ricardo looks at Jennifer.
Jennifer looks at Maya.
For the first time in a long time...
The silence isn't filled with distance.
It's filled with understanding.
Ricardo leans forward.
Salamat...
sa pagiging honest sa amin, nak.
Hindi siguro madaling sabihin lahat ng 'yan.
Maya slowly shakes her head.
Hindi po.
Ricardo nods.
He glances at Jennifer.
Giving her the chance to speak.
Jennifer takes a slow, shaky breath.
She looks at her daughter.
Really looks at her.
For the first time...
Not as a student.
Not as someone who has to succeed.
But simply...
As Maya.
Jennifer opens her mouth to speak...
The room remains silent.
Jennifer looks at Maya.
For a long moment...
She struggles to find the right words.
Not because she has nothing to say.
But because she realizes she has spent years speaking...
Without truly listening.
Ricardo quietly waits beside them.
He doesn't interrupt.
Jennifer slowly exhales.
...
Nung sinabi mo lahat...
Ang una kong naisip... Saan ako nagkulang?
Maya looks at her mother.
Surprised.
update Jennifer (glad)
Jennifer gives a small, bittersweet smile.
Akala ko...
Kapag napagtapos kita...
Kapag nabigyan kita ng magandang trabaho...
Kapag naging secure ang future mo...
Magiging okay ka.
Pause.
'Yon lang ang nasa isip ko.
Every single day.
Her voice begins to tremble.
Hindi ko naitanong...
Kung masaya ka ba.
Maya lowers her gaze.
update Jennifer (teary)
Jennifer's eyes begin to fill with tears.
[signal arg="drain:on"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Nakita ko lahat ng drawings mo.
Lahat.
Pause.
Alam mo ba kung ano'ng una kong naalala?
Maya slowly shakes her head.
Jennifer smiles through her tears.
No'ng maliit ka...
Hindi ka mapakali kapag walang papel.
Kahit resibo...
Dinodrawingan mo.
Ricardo chuckles softly.
Totoo.
Pati likod ng electric bill natin.
Maya lets out a small laugh.
update Jennifer (glad)
Jennifer smiles.
The laughter lasts only a second.
Then her expression softens again.
Naalala ko rin...
Nung sinabi mong gusto mong maging artist.
Pause.
Naalala ko kung paano kita pinigilan.
Maya immediately shakes her head.
Ma—
(Jennifer gently raises a hand.
Asking Maya to let her finish.)
Hindi...
Hayaan mo muna ako.
Pause.
Akala ko...
Pinoprotektahan kita.
Ayokong dumating 'yung araw na mag-aalala ka kung saan kukuha ng pangkain.
Kung may trabaho ka pa kinabukasan.
Her tears finally fall.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Kaya pinili ko para sa'yo...
Ang akala kong mas ligtas.
Pero...
Hindi ko naisip...
Na baka habang pinoprotektahan kita...
Unti-unti kitang nawawala.
The room falls silent.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
update Maya (teary)
Maya's eyes begin to water.
update Jennifer (teary)
Jennifer wipes her tears with trembling hands.
Anak...
I'm sorry.
Pause.
I'm so...
so sorry.
Maya stares at her mother.
She has imagined this conversation countless times.
But she never imagined hearing those words.
Ma...
Hindi lang naman ikaw.
Ako rin.
I should've told you sooner.
Instead...
Tinago ko lahat.
Nagsinungaling ako.
Natakot ako.
Jennifer immediately shakes her head.
Hindi ka nagsinungaling dahil masama kang anak.
Natakot ka...
Dahil natakot kitang magsabi ng totoo.
Her own words hit her hard.
She looks away.
Ashamed.
Ricardo quietly stands.
He walks toward both of them.
Standing between mother and daughter.
Pwede ba...
Ako naman.
The two women look at him.
Ricardo scratches the back of his neck awkwardly.
A habit he always has whenever emotions become difficult.
Alam n'yo...
Hindi rin ako naging magaling.
Maya looks surprised.
Akala ko...
Basta nagtatrabaho ako.
Basta naibibigay ko kailangan n'yo.
Okay na.
Pause.
Pero...
Hindi ko rin napansin...
Na habang busy akong maghanapbuhay...
May anak pala akong unti-unting nawawalan ng kumpiyansa sa sarili.
May asawa ako na kailangan kong suportahan kahit ano.
Maya's eyes begin to well with tears again.
[signal arg="heartbeat:on"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Naalala ko...
No'ng nasa shop tayo nila Ethan.
Pause.
Lagi ko siyang pinupuri.
Hindi dahil mas mahalaga siya.
Hindi dahil mas magaling siya kaysa sa'yo.
Hindi ko lang alam...
Na bawat salitang sinasabi ko...
Naririnig mo rin.
update Maya (soft)
Maya lowers her head.
She remembers every compliment.
Every laugh.
Every photograph.
Kung alam ko lang na nasasaktan ka...
Mas iningatan ko sana.
Pause.
I'm sorry, anak.
Maya can no longer hold back.
She quietly wipes away the tears rolling down her cheeks.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Hindi ko naman gusto na sisihin kayo.
Promise.
I know you both only wanted what's best for me.
I know...
Lahat ng ginawa n'yo...
Para sa'kin.
Pause.
Pero...
Hindi ko na rin alam kung sino ako.
I kept trying to become the daughter I thought you wanted.
The words hang heavily in the room.
Jennifer slowly reaches forward.
She hesitates.
Instinctively, she glances toward it.
For a brief moment...
Her hand almost moves to check the notification.
She stops herself.
Jennifer quietly shakes her head.
Not now.
She looks back at Maya.
Unsure if Maya will accept the gesture.
After a brief moment...
Maya reaches out too.
Their hands meet.
Jennifer gently holds her daughter's hand.
Tightly.
As if afraid to let go again.
Maya: ...
Hindi ko maipapangako...
Na matatanggap ko agad lahat.
Pause.
Matatakot pa rin ako.
Mag-aalala pa rin ako.
Nanay pa rin ako.
A small laugh escapes Maya.
update Jennifer (glad)
Jennifer smiles.
Pero...
Susubukan kong makinig. Hindi lang magsalita.
Makinig.
Sa gusto mo.
Sa nararamdaman mo.
At sa mga pangarap mo.
update Maya (teary)
Maya smiles through her tears.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
'Yon lang naman po ang gusto ko.
Na marinig kayo saken.
Ricardo smiles warmly.
He places a hand on both of their shoulders.
Bringing them together.
For the first time in what feels like forever...
The silence inside the house no longer feels heavy.
It feels...
Hopeful.
A knock interrupts the moment.
[signal arg="sfx:knock"]
KNOCK. KNOCK.
[signal arg="sfx:knock"]
The three turn toward the front door.
Ricardo chuckles.
Mukhang alam ko na kung sino.
He walks toward the entrance.
Jennifer gently lets go of Maya's hand.
But not completely.
Their fingers briefly linger.
A silent promise.
That this time...
Neither of them will let the other carry everything alone.
To actually listen to one another.
And to be present in aware.
Ricardo opens the front door.
Ethan stands outside, holding a plastic container.
He smiles sheepishly.
Uh...
Bad timing ba?
May dala lang sana akong kare-kare.
update Maya (glad)
Maya laughs.
A real laugh.
The first one that fills the entire house.
Ricardo grins.
Hindi.
Sakto lang.
Halika. Pumasok ka ng nga.
Ethan looks around.
He notices the tearful faces.
[signal arg="heartbeat:off"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
He immediately becomes awkward.
... Mukhang may na-interrupt yata ako.
update Maya (teary)
Maya wipes her eyes and chuckles.
Konti lang.
Okay...
Pwede bang magpanggap tayong walang umiyak?
The room erupts into soft laughter.
Not because everything is fixed.
But because...
For the first time...
They are laughing together.
The room erupts into soft laughter.
Nobody reaches for a phone.
Nobody tries to capture the moment.
For once...
Being present is enough.
Not because everything is fixed.
But because...
For the first time...
They are laughing together.
The family now sits around the dining table once again.
The atmosphere is noticeably lighter than before.
Not because the problems have disappeared...
But because no one is pretending they don't exist.
Ethan places the container of kare-kare on the table.
Good thing hindi natapon.
Sayang naman.
Laughing.
'Yan pa talaga inalala mo.
Mahal kaya kare-kare.
Jennifer stands.
She quietly walks to the kitchen.
A moment later, she returns carrying plates and bowls.
Without saying a word...
She begins setting the table.
Maya notices.
She immediately stands.)
Ma...
Ako na po.
Jennifer looks at her.
She hesitates for a second.
Then nods.
Sige. Salamat,nak.
Together, they begin arranging the table.
It's a simple task.
But the silence between them no longer feels uncomfortable.
It's gentle.
Careful.
As if both are slowly learning how to be around each other again.
A few minutes later.
Everyone sits back down.
No one begins eating yet.
The conversation naturally resumes.
So...
Ano'ng plano natin?
The question hangs in the air.
Maya takes a deep breath.
[signal arg="sfx:breath_shaky"]
Honestly...
Hindi ko pa po alam.
I just know...
I don't think I can continue pretending.
Jennifer quietly listens.
No interruptions.
No immediate advice.
Just listening.
May naiisip ka bang gawin?
Maya nods slowly.
I've been thinking...
Maybe...
mag-shift.
Or...
take some time muna para makapag-isip nang maayos.
I don't want to make another decision just because I'm scared.
update Jennifer (worried)
Jennifer lowers her gaze.
She gently folds her hands together.
Matatakot pa rin ako.
Maya looks at her.
Hindi mawawala 'yon.
Nanay ako.
Normal lang siguro.
Pause.
Pero...
Ayoko na ring ikaw ang matakot sa'kin.
The words catch Maya off guard.
update Jennifer (glad)
Jennifer smiles faintly.
Kung gusto mong mag-explore...
We'll figure it out.
Hindi man agad...
Pero...
Sabay natin hahanapin.
Maya's eyes begin to water.
Thank you, Ma.
Jennifer reaches across the table.
She gently squeezes Maya's hand.
This time...
Neither of them hesitates.
Ricardo smiles warmly.
Hindi rin naman kailangan maayos agad lahat.
Life doesn't work like that.
Pause.
Ang importante...
Hindi mo haharapin mag-isa.
Maya nods.
A weight she has carried for months...
Feels just a little lighter.
Ethan quietly watches the family.
A proud smile forms on his face.
Pwede ba akong magsabi?
All eyes turn to him.
Growing up...
Akala ko kailangan alam mo na agad kung ano'ng gusto mong gawin sa buhay.
Kung anong course.
Kung anong trabaho.
Kung anong future.
Pause.
Pero...
After everything that happened sa family namin...
Na-realize ko...
Walang may complete roadmap.
Lahat tayo...
Naghahanap lang din.
Maya listens intently.
Hindi ka late.
Hindi ka failure.
You're just...
finding your own path.
update Maya (smile)
Maya smiles.
Ang lalim ah.
Nag-practice ka ba bago pumunta rito?
Ethan shrugs dramatically.
Oo.
Tatlong oras.
Ricardo laughs.
Sinungaling.
Ethan grins.
Mga two minutes lang.
The room fills with laughter.
A comfortable silence follows.
A notification quietly buzzes from Jennifer's phone.
She instinctively reaches for it.
Her fingers stop midway.
She glances at her family.
Then back at the screen.
After a brief moment...
She quietly turns the phone face down.
Leaving it untouched.
Only then does she look back at all of them.
Jennifer glances toward Maya.
...
Pwede ko bang makita...
'yung mga drawings mo?
Maya blinks.
Surprised.
Talaga?
Jennifer nods.
Kung okay lang sa'yo.
Maya smiles.
A genuine...
hopeful smile.
Sige po.
Pero...
Huwag n'yo pong i-judge 'yung mga luma.
Naku.
Excited na nga akong makita.
Ako rin.
May exclusive gallery opening pala rito.
update Maya (glad)
Maya laughs.
Libre lang entrance.
Pero bawal harsh critics.
Ay.
Uuwi na lang pala ako.
Maya lightly throws a table napkin at him.
Loko.
Ethan catches it effortlessly.
The room echoes with laughter once again.
Not forced.
Just...
Natural.
leave Jennifer [animation="Instant Out"]
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
Maya opens the drawer that had remained locked for months.
She gently takes out her ipad.
She pauses.
Before...
She hid it because she was afraid.
Now...
She carries it into the living room.
Not to prove anything.
Not to seek approval.
But to share a part of herself she had hidden for far too long.
As she steps out of her room...
Her family waits.
Patiently.
Ready to listen.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The golden light of sunset shines through the dining room window.
The familiar dining table sits in the center of the room.
The same family.
But something feels different.
Jennifer carries the last bowl from the kitchen.
Ricardo follows behind with freshly cooked rice.
Maya places glasses of water on the table.
No one tells anyone what to do.
They simply help each other.
Ethan stands nearby, about to leave.
He slings his backpack over one shoulder.
Sige...
Aalis na 'ko.
Baka hinahanap na rin ako ni Mama.
Ricardo walks him to the door.
Salamat, hijo.
Hindi lang sa pagdala ng kare-kare.
Ethan smiles.
He knows what Ricardo really means.
Wala 'yon, Tito.
In the background, Maya walks over.
Text mo 'ko pag-uwi.
Oo naman.
Tsaka...
Half-smiling.
Huwag mong kalimutan.
May utang ka pang drawing sa'kin.
Maya rolls her eyes.
Demanding.
Professional client ako.
Maya laughs.
Sige na.
Ingat.
Ethan gives one last wave before stepping outside.
The front door closes.
The house becomes quiet again.
Not an uncomfortable silence.
Just...
Peaceful.
The family gathers around the table.
Jennifer instinctively reaches for her phone...
The screen immediately lights up.
Several social media notifications.
Comments.
Reactions.
For a brief moment...
Her thumb hovers over the screen.
Ready to unlock it.
She stops.
A quiet breath escapes her.
Her eyes drift toward Maya...
Who is silently arranging the plates on the table.
Jennifer lowers her gaze.
A faint, almost embarrassed smile crosses her face.
As if realizing...
"Ito na naman."
She gently locks the screen.
Then walks over to the nearby counter.
And carefully places the phone face down.
She leaves it there.
Ricardo notices.
He looks at his own phone.
A work notification appears.
He reads it for a second.
Then quietly locks the screen.
Without saying anything...
Places it beside Jennifer's.
Face down.
Maya watches them.
She smiles to herself.
Then reaches into her hoodie pocket.
She places hers beside theirs.
Three phones.
Left untouched.
Jennifer looks at Maya.
Kanin?
Ako na po.
Maya takes the rice and serves Jennifer first.
Then Ricardo.
Lastly herself.
Ricardo begins eating.
After a bite...
Parang mas masarap 'yung luto ngayon ah.
Jennifer raises an eyebrow.
Pareho lang naman.
Hindi.
May secret ingredient.
Maya looks up.
Ano?
Ricardo shrugs.
Hindi nagmamadali.
Jennifer lets out a quiet laugh.
Drama mo.
Eh totoo naman.
They continue eating.
A comfortable silence settles over the table.
Not because nobody has anything to say.
But because nobody feels pressured to fill it.
After a while...
Jennifer looks at Maya.
May naisip ka na ano gagawin mo?
Maya chews for a moment before answering.
Meron.
Ano?
Maya glances around the table.
At her parents.
At the food.
At the empty chair Ethan had been sitting on moments ago.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
She smiles.
Mamaya na.
Secret muna.
Aba.
May surprise pala.
Malay n'yo.
Impossible.
Mana sa nanay mo.
Jennifer lightly nudges Ricardo.
Bolero.
Ricardo grins.
Effective pa rin.
Jennifer shakes her head, trying not to smile.
She fails.
Maya quietly watches them.
For the first time in a long while...
Their laughter doesn't feel distant.
It doesn't compete with notification sounds.
Or glowing screens.
It's just...
There.
Real.
Present.
Maya leans back slightly.
She looks at the three phones resting silently on the counter.
No notifications are checked.
No scrolling.
No distractions.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:angry:2"]
Just dinner.
Her eyes soften.
A small smile forms.
Not because everything is perfect.
It isn't.
Tomorrow will still bring difficult conversations.
There will still be uncertainty.
There will still be fears.
But tonight...
They chose to sit together.
To listen.
To laugh.
To be present.
Maya quietly picks up her glass.
Ma.
Pa.
Salamat.
Jennifer and Ricardo look at her.
Jennifer smiles.
A simple...
Mother's smile.
Kain na.
Lumalamig na.
Maya chuckles.
Opo.
The three continue eating.
The voices become softer.
Pieces of conversation overlap naturally.
'Wag mo nga ubusin lahat ng kare-kare.
Eh ang dami n'yo kasing kanin.
Ay nako, pareho lang kayong makulit.
The laughter continues.
The camera reaches the hallway.
Family photographs line the wall.
Among them...
An old photo of the Ilagans.
No phones.
Just smiles.
The camera lingers.
Then slowly fades to black.
THE END.

[signal arg="drain:off"]
jump act_ending/
